name: Abomasnow
flavorText: The Pokémon is known to bring blizzards. A shake of its massive body is enough to cause whiteout conditions.
Ability1Text: Your Single Strike Pokémon in play, except any Abomasnow, get +50 HP. You can't apply more than 1 Toughness Boost Ability at a time.

name: Flapple
flavorText: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you placed any damage counters in this way, shuffle this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Kingdra
flavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.
Ability1Text: When your Active Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, you may move any amount of Water Energy from that Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Frosmoth
flavorText: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Water Pokémon.

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and attach any number of basic Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Put the other cards into your hand.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Wyrdeer
flavorText: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Falinks
flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Rapid Strike Pokémon in play.

name: Kleavor
flavorText: A violent creature that fells towering trees with its crude axes and shields itself with hard stone. If one should chance upon this Pokémon in the wilds, one's only recourse is to flee.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
Ability1Text: If your opponent has any Pokémon VMAX in play, this Pokémon's attacks cost ColorlessColorlessColorless less.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Obstagoon
flavorText: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Metal Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
Ability1Text: Basic Energy attached to your Benched Pokémon can't be discarded by an effect of your opponent's Item or Supporter cards.

name: Starmie V
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Ice Rider Calyrex VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Galarian Articuno V
Ability1Text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Shadow Rider Calyrex V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Special Energy or Stadium cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon and put 5 damage counters on each of them.

name: Shadow Rider Calyrex VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Psychic Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Galarian Zapdos V
Ability1Text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Pokémon V in play.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Galarian Moltres V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Darkness Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Direflame Wings Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Zacian V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to this Pokémon. Put the other cards into your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Zamazenta V
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon VMAX.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Garchomp V
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 220 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Ice Rider Calyrex VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: You may discard up to 2 Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Shadow Rider Calyrex VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Psychic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Psychic Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Psychic Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.
